<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-81-0290 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Nuclear Safety Commission has been established as an advisory organwhich is responsible for the regulatory aspect in accordance with therevision of the Atomic Energy Basic Law Act in 1978, separately fromthe Atomic Energy Commission which had been in charge of both developmentand regulations. At the same time, the whole system of safety regulationshas been reformed. An outline of the roles of the Nuclear Safety Commissionis presented here. Further, described are the system of regulations,operational experience, the state of the safety study, and the presentsituation of systems for the disaster prevention, etc. associated withthe nuclear power station in Japan, and how the Commission relates tothese matters is discussed.</TEXT></DOC>